1
00:01:30,940 --> 00:01:33,958
[Episode 8]

2
00:01:38,799 --> 00:01:40,679
Where are you going?

3
00:01:40,679 --> 00:01:42,039
It's the New Year.

4
00:01:42,039 --> 00:01:43,959
They're setting off fireworks on the rooftop.

5
00:01:43,959 --> 00:01:45,640
Let's watch it together.

6
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,280
That's not likely.

7
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:58,120
A bunch of brothers are waiting
to celebrate the New Year with me.

8
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:00,039
Then why come to my place?

9
00:02:08,879 --> 00:02:11,520
I still have to get back.

10
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,880
No.

11
00:02:22,599 --> 00:02:24,039
You're not fully recovered yet.

12
00:02:24,039 --> 00:02:26,120
And you've been drinking again.

13
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,920
Stay at my place tonight.

14
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,640
Xia Liu Yi.

15
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:47,040
Why do you look so guilty?

16
00:03:03,159 --> 00:03:05,240
I don't.

17
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:07,439
Fine, let's just watch the fireworks.

18
00:03:30,879 --> 00:03:34,480
Why didn't you bring Mei back for the New Year?

19
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:39,999
Mr. He seems really eager to see her.

20
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,839
We broke up.

21
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,985
I haven't had the chance to tell Dad yet.

22
00:03:47,985 --> 00:03:49,945
You're the first to know.

23
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,879
What?

24
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:57,399
Didn't you show me that tattoo this morning?

25
00:03:58,199 --> 00:03:59,880
She already likes someone else.

26
00:04:09,719 --> 00:04:11,159
Xia Liu Yi.

27
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:15,360
You can't force someone to like you.

28
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,119
And you can't pretend
you don't like someone either.

29
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:37,160
If she likes someone, so be it.

30
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:39,519
I'll introduce you to someone else.

31
00:04:39,519 --> 00:04:42,280
You'll move on by then.

32
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:48,639
It's so beautiful.

33
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,519
Xia Liu Yi.

34
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:54,199
Happy New Year.

35
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,960
Happy New Year, He Chu San.

36
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:55,480
According to our informant in the underworld,

37
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,959
more than a decade ago,

38
00:05:56,959 --> 00:05:58,519
the name "Old Shopkeeper"

39
00:05:58,519 --> 00:06:01,600
was already known throughout
the entire underworld.

40
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,959
Whoever he wanted dead
would quickly fall into ruin.

41
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:08,199
And whoever he favored
would rise to great success.

42
00:06:08,199 --> 00:06:09,720
On both sides of the law,

43
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:12,759
everyone followed his will.

44
00:06:12,759 --> 00:06:16,120
However, no one has ever seen
the Old Shopkeeper's real face.

45
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:20,480
Many people believe he's
just an underworld legend.

46
00:06:22,879 --> 00:06:25,119
- That's all?
- Yep, that's all.

47
00:06:27,279 --> 00:06:31,000
That old fox Lu Guang Ming wouldn't casually

48
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,520
ask me to investigate a mere legend.

49
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:38,639
Inspector Xie, are you done with work?

50
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:42,480
Dad, you're here.

51
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:44,319
You didn't even come home
for New Year's Eve dinner.

52
00:06:44,319 --> 00:06:47,480
So, I'm here at the police station
to drag you back.

53
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,960
Hello, sir.

54
00:06:51,519 --> 00:06:52,959
I've been busy with a case.

55
00:06:52,959 --> 00:06:54,680
I'll head back as soon as I have time.

56
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,240
Busy, busy, busy.

57
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:59,959
You're even busier than me,
the Deputy Commissioner.

58
00:06:59,959 --> 00:07:04,959
So, I've brought New Year's Eve dinner
to the station for you.

59
00:07:04,959 --> 00:07:06,679
Sit down.

60
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:13,119
I asked Madam Wang
to cook your favorite dishes.

61
00:07:14,839 --> 00:07:16,280
Thank you, Dad.

62
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:20,319
You need a full stomach to investigate cases.

63
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:21,720
By the way...

64
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,560
How have you been lately?

65
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,079
With the council elections coming up,

66
00:07:25,079 --> 00:07:26,840
you must be very busy.

67
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:31,560
Yes, things are different now.

68
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,800
The lease period is almost up,

69
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,879
and those foreigners are watching very closely.

70
00:07:34,879 --> 00:07:36,319
The superintendents and inspectors below

71
00:07:36,319 --> 00:07:38,399
also have to go through reshuffles.

72
00:07:38,399 --> 00:07:42,360
So, this old body of mine
has to keep running nonstop as well.

73
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:51,279
By the way, have you been
investigating Inspector Hua lately?

74
00:07:51,279 --> 00:07:53,040
What's going on with him?

75
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,240
He wouldn't be connected to

76
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:58,720
the criminals you're investigating, would he?

77
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:03,600
No, it's just a routine check.

78
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,680
There's no evidence proving that Inspector Hua

79
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,759
is colluding with criminals.

80
00:08:07,759 --> 00:08:10,720
I've already mentioned
all of this in the case report.

81
00:08:12,199 --> 00:08:14,079
Yes, I know.

82
00:08:14,079 --> 00:08:18,480
In the police force, there are also
some gray areas that are hard to explain.

83
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:21,079
How could a report possibly make that clear?

84
00:08:24,079 --> 00:08:25,639
Here's the thing.

85
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:29,920
Recently, I've been placed in charge
of the superintendent rotation.

86
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:35,759
But the candidates' records
all seem to be flawless.

87
00:08:35,759 --> 00:08:38,000
No one is telling me the truth.

88
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:42,319
So, I can only come and ask my own son.

89
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:45,080
Dad.

90
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:48,279
We're just following the rules.

91
00:08:48,279 --> 00:08:53,399
Without any evidence,
I can't say anything either.

92
00:08:53,399 --> 00:08:54,639
All right, all right.

93
00:08:54,639 --> 00:08:57,879
My son follows the rules better than I do.

94
00:08:57,879 --> 00:09:00,679
Your dad is ashamed to admit he can't compare.

95
00:09:00,679 --> 00:09:03,519
By the way, in this round of rotations,

96
00:09:03,519 --> 00:09:06,720
several chief inspector positions
in different districts have opened up.

97
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:09,160
Have you thought about going for one?

98
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,360
Dad.

99
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:18,120
I don't want to rely on connections.

100
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:23,639
Besides, I'm doing well
in the Organized Crime Bureau.

101
00:09:23,639 --> 00:09:25,800
I like working on the front line.

102
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:30,200
I don't like sitting in an office.

103
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,399
You really are my son.

104
00:09:32,399 --> 00:09:34,240
You've got backbone.

105
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,399
But remember this,

106
00:09:36,399 --> 00:09:39,720
if there's anything you can't decide
or need help with,

107
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,719
just tell your dad anytime.

108
00:09:44,759 --> 00:09:46,120
More than a decade ago,

109
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,200
the name "Old Shopkeeper"

110
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,920
was already known
throughout the entire underworld.

111
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:54,599
Dad, have you ever heard of...

112
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,679
Heard of what?

113
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:02,679
"New tides replace the old."

114
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,879
If I get promoted through your connections,

115
00:10:05,879 --> 00:10:08,799
then I wouldn't be the wave
pushing the old one aside.

116
00:10:08,799 --> 00:10:10,279
You brat.

117
00:10:10,279 --> 00:10:12,360
So, you think you've grown wings now, huh?

118
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,919
If you're not eating, I'll take it back.

119
00:10:13,919 --> 00:10:15,520
I'll eat, I'll eat!

120
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:16,559
Dad, sit down first.

121
00:10:16,559 --> 00:10:17,719
Sit.

122
00:10:29,305 --> 00:10:30,651
[Xiaoqi Trading]

123
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,080
Move it, move it. Hurry up.

124
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,240
Hurry up, hurry up.

125
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,839
Come on, hurry.

126
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:43,240
Liu Yi, I left you a message the other day
saying I'd come tonight.

127
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,520
I've got something on today. Go back quickly.

128
00:10:46,917 --> 00:10:48,198
Hello?

129
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:51,120
Sirs, please go inside.

130
00:12:16,519 --> 00:12:19,320
Just wait and see how I'll deal with you.

131
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:21,359
Just wait.

132
00:12:33,639 --> 00:12:34,759
What are you looking at?

133
00:12:34,759 --> 00:12:36,600
Looking at you.

134
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,480
Think I'm scared of you? Go ahead, make a move.

135
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,959
Come on.

136
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,520
Go in.

137
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,760
You wait here.

138
00:12:52,159 --> 00:12:53,519
Why are you pushing?

139
00:12:53,519 --> 00:12:55,079
So what?

140
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,240
Liu Yi.

141
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,360
- Inspector.
- Little brother.

142
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,879
You haven't come by the house in a while.

143
00:13:38,879 --> 00:13:40,919
Long time no see.

144
00:13:40,919 --> 00:13:42,320
Old Qi.

145
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:44,279
- Hua.
- Eat a little less.

146
00:13:44,279 --> 00:13:45,519
Your belly's bigger than mine now.

147
00:13:45,519 --> 00:13:46,919
- Look at yourself.
- I can't help it.

148
00:13:46,919 --> 00:13:48,160
Sit.

149
00:13:49,879 --> 00:13:51,360
We're all brothers here.

150
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,400
Just say what you need to say.

151
00:13:59,519 --> 00:14:02,359
You all know about
the council elections, right?

152
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:07,960
Hong Kong isn't what it used to be.

153
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:11,279
In a few years, the lease
on the territory will expire.

154
00:14:11,279 --> 00:14:13,960
The higher-ups have
put forward many conditions.

155
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:17,480
Liu Yi, the demolition of Ganglong Walled City

156
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:19,439
is one of those conditions.

157
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,959
And there's also me.

158
00:14:24,679 --> 00:14:28,240
My successor was supposed to be chosen by me.

159
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:31,320
But now, the higher-ups won't approve it.

160
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:33,559
The Organized Crime Bureau
arrested Sha Lao San some time ago.

161
00:14:33,559 --> 00:14:36,680
The ICAC has been making a lot of moves lately.

162
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:41,520
A lot of eyes are on me, and on you as well.

163
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:45,639
At a time like this, not only are you refusing
to join forces and help each other,

164
00:14:45,639 --> 00:14:48,279
but you're fighting among yourselves?

165
00:14:48,279 --> 00:14:50,480
Hua, when has the Hesheng Society

166
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:53,480
ever been on the same side as Xiaoqi Hall?

167
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:57,799
Ten years ago, Hesheng swore a blood oath.

168
00:14:57,799 --> 00:14:59,679
We pledged before heaven
and acknowledged our founding masters.

169
00:14:59,679 --> 00:15:01,120
By seniority,

170
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:04,320
Xiaoqi Hall wouldn't even
qualify to step through the door.

171
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,879
When Qing Long was still alive,

172
00:15:05,879 --> 00:15:07,480
he didn't dare offend me either.

173
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:09,600
Now Xia Xiao Liu is crossing the line
and stepping onto my turf.

174
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:11,760
What's that supposed to mean?

175
00:15:15,639 --> 00:15:17,559
Times change.

176
00:15:17,559 --> 00:15:21,480
Circumstances make heroes, Qi.

177
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:25,000
As for Hong Kong, it's only so big.

178
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:28,200
Naturally, whoever's capable calls the shots.

179
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:31,479
Just because you say it's yours
doesn't make it yours.

180
00:15:32,679 --> 00:15:34,399
I get it now.

181
00:15:34,399 --> 00:15:36,200
Your name must be written all over it.

182
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:38,960
Xia Liu Yi, you don't think
I'm afraid of you, do you?

183
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,039
Old Qi.

184
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:41,959
Let's talk it out calmly.

185
00:15:44,879 --> 00:15:46,319
Sit down.

186
00:15:51,759 --> 00:15:53,559
If you keep arguing like this,

187
00:15:53,559 --> 00:15:56,279
and I can't hold things down,

188
00:15:56,279 --> 00:16:00,879
someone will seize my weakness
and bring me down.

189
00:16:00,879 --> 00:16:04,399
Then none of us will have it easy.

190
00:16:04,399 --> 00:16:06,319
Hua!

191
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,480
Everyone in Hong Kong knows

192
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:12,120
that you belong to the Old Shopkeeper.

193
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:13,919
Right now, you're helping the Old Shopkeeper

194
00:16:13,919 --> 00:16:15,919
manage both sides of the law.

195
00:16:15,919 --> 00:16:18,439
Who would dare touch you?

196
00:16:26,399 --> 00:16:27,919
The Old Shopkeeper

197
00:16:27,919 --> 00:16:30,799
is the one strategizing behind the scenes.

198
00:16:30,799 --> 00:16:33,760
Trivial matters like ours wouldn't concern him.

199
00:16:35,559 --> 00:16:36,919
It's a pity for me.

200
00:16:36,919 --> 00:16:38,759
I've worked hard and contributed a lot,

201
00:16:38,759 --> 00:16:41,559
yet in the end I still can't compete with

202
00:16:41,559 --> 00:16:44,079
those who were simply born lucky.

203
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,919
Logically speaking,

204
00:16:47,919 --> 00:16:50,480
the superintendent list
should've been finalized long ago.

205
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:53,200
But there's been no news from Kowloon.

206
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:56,639
Inspector Hua, does that Xie boy

207
00:16:56,639 --> 00:16:58,640
have his eyes on your position?

208
00:17:02,279 --> 00:17:04,279
Forget about whether he's a Xie or not.

209
00:17:04,279 --> 00:17:06,519
If he dares to touch Hua,

210
00:17:06,519 --> 00:17:09,440
I, Fei Qi, will be the first to deal with him.

211
00:17:14,039 --> 00:17:15,480
So, what exactly should we do?

212
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:17,720
Inspector Hua, what do you suggest?

213
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:21,480
What exactly to do depends on the two of you.

214
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:23,200
I'm just an inspector.

215
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,040
How would I know?

216
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:36,480
You two take your time talking.

217
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:39,040
I'll go to the restroom first.

218
00:17:41,279 --> 00:17:43,720
I'll be counting on you in the future.

219
00:18:33,039 --> 00:18:34,559
Stop. You can't go in there.

220
00:18:34,559 --> 00:18:36,200
Someone ordered fish. I have to deliver it.

221
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:38,000
Police investigation.

222
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:02,279
Senior Inspector Xie Jia Hua
from the Organized Crime Bureau.

223
00:19:02,279 --> 00:19:03,400
We've been investigating this gang conflict

224
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,599
for quite some time.

225
00:19:04,599 --> 00:19:06,519
You can leave this to the OCB.

226
00:19:06,519 --> 00:19:09,160
This isn't just a gang fight anymore.

227
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,400
There's been a murder inside.

228
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,879
Take me to the scene.

229
00:20:16,839 --> 00:20:18,839
Yeah, the scene was brutal.

230
00:20:18,839 --> 00:20:21,280
Yeah, I never expected it.

231
00:20:26,519 --> 00:20:27,720
Hurry up, they're calling us over.

232
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:29,640
Coming.

233
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:31,640
Why are you here?

234
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:32,960
Let's go.

235
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:35,319
Hurry and seal off the scene. Move quickly.

236
00:20:35,319 --> 00:20:37,079
- All right, all right.
- Hurry up.

237
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:55,799
What happened?

238
00:20:55,799 --> 00:20:56,960
None of your business.

239
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,520
Let's leave first.

240
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:16,359
Inspector Xie, what brings you here?

241
00:21:16,359 --> 00:21:19,240
Don't tell me you checked my duty roster

242
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:20,720
just to arrange a private meeting with me.

243
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:23,520
I want the complete file
on the Tang Jia Qi case.

244
00:21:25,839 --> 00:21:28,079
Inspector Xie, why the sudden interest
in this old case?

245
00:21:28,079 --> 00:21:29,480
Don't waste my time.

246
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:33,000
I suspect it's highly connected
to a police death case I'm currently handling.

247
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,119
I have the authority
to reopen the investigation.

248
00:21:34,119 --> 00:21:35,480
Give me the file.

249
00:21:41,839 --> 00:21:45,000
File number 050038.

250
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,640
The victim, Tang Jia Qi,

251
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,960
was a senior investigator with the ICAC.

252
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:52,079
During the investigation,

253
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:56,720
he was strangled to death with an iron chain.

254
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:05,319
I also heard that you two
were very close back then.

255
00:22:05,319 --> 00:22:09,040
You had the best chemistry among your cohort.

256
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:15,480
After a joint police investigation,

257
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:18,920
the case concluded that
Tang Jia Qi, while undercover,

258
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:22,800
was caught in a gang shootout
and died in the line of duty.

259
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:32,359
All suspects involved were arrested.

260
00:22:32,359 --> 00:22:36,480
The evidence chain was complete,
and the case was closed perfectly.

261
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:43,960
The files have long been archived.

262
00:22:44,839 --> 00:22:46,839
There were many doubts about this case.

263
00:22:46,839 --> 00:22:49,040
It should never have been closed.

264
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:53,599
That's not something
a small investigator like me

265
00:22:53,599 --> 00:22:55,279
needs to worry about.

266
00:22:55,279 --> 00:22:56,599
Inspector Xie.

267
00:22:57,359 --> 00:23:01,960
Even though we're close...

268
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:03,319
I'm...

269
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:08,279
Sorry, Inspector Xie.

270
00:23:08,279 --> 00:23:11,559
According to regulations, this is top secret.

271
00:23:11,559 --> 00:23:12,960
We must have written authorization

272
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,799
from the Governor's Office.

273
00:23:14,799 --> 00:23:16,240
I'll ask you one more time.

274
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:18,040
Are you going to give it to me or not?

275
00:23:24,559 --> 00:23:27,799
Tang Jia Qi died
such a horrible death back then.

276
00:23:27,799 --> 00:23:31,799
Where were you
when the case was hastily closed?

277
00:23:31,799 --> 00:23:34,599
His remains have long turned to ashes.

278
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:37,639
And now you suddenly come here making a scene.

279
00:23:38,319 --> 00:23:40,839
Don't you think that's a bit hypocritical?

280
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:47,839
Inspector Xie, just look at yourself.

281
00:23:47,839 --> 00:23:50,520
What about the rules
you're always talking about?

282
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:54,880
What about the procedures
you treat like the Bible?

283
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:57,039
Even if you get the file, so what?

284
00:23:57,039 --> 00:23:58,080
If it doesn't follow procedure,

285
00:23:58,080 --> 00:24:00,480
you still won't be able to do anything.

286
00:24:02,079 --> 00:24:05,760
Since you chose to be
a righteous police officer...

287
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:11,720
then stick with being powerless.

288
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:14,559
Trying to have it both ways

289
00:24:14,559 --> 00:24:17,720
will only make you more hypocritical.

290
00:24:33,799 --> 00:24:36,599
Don't let me find out that
these two cases are directly connected.

291
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:41,599
If I find the evidence,
no one will be able to stop me.

292
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:46,480
We'll see.

293
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:03,599
The gift for you...

294
00:25:04,559 --> 00:25:07,280
It's time to deliver it.

295
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:40,000
Find informants from Hesheng and Xiaoqi for me.

296
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:42,760
I want Xia Liu Yi and Fei Qi dug out.

297
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,480
He Chu San.

298
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,599
You've made it now.

299
00:26:15,599 --> 00:26:18,079
You've got a house and a car.

300
00:26:19,519 --> 00:26:21,720
Does investment banking
really make that much money?

301
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:24,400
If I'd known, I would've gone into it, too.

302
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:25,963
This apartment is rented.

303
00:26:25,963 --> 00:26:27,519
It's close to my office.

304
00:26:27,519 --> 00:26:29,160
The car is second-hand.

305
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:32,000
We often visit clients, so we need it a lot.

306
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:34,880
Come, sit down.

307
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:36,760
The wound needs to be disinfected.

308
00:26:42,599 --> 00:26:43,960
I'll help you.

309
00:26:56,079 --> 00:26:57,800
- I'll do it myself.
- Don't move.

310
00:27:55,559 --> 00:27:57,519
There's a piece of glass here.

311
00:27:57,519 --> 00:27:59,359
It's stuck in pretty deep.

312
00:28:00,079 --> 00:28:02,039
It might hurt a little.

313
00:28:02,039 --> 00:28:03,279
I've taken bullet wounds before.

314
00:28:03,279 --> 00:28:04,680
This is nothing.

315
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:06,399
I'm not afraid at all.

316
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:10,119
Did I hurt you?

317
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:13,079
It's fine.

318
00:28:13,079 --> 00:28:14,440
It doesn't hurt.

319
00:28:19,079 --> 00:28:22,119
Why are you being so rough?

320
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:14,160
Are you all right?

321
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:15,879
I'm fine.

322
00:29:22,119 --> 00:29:23,960
How did you end up hurt like this?

323
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:26,039
What exactly happened?

324
00:29:26,039 --> 00:29:28,799
Why are the police all looking for you?

325
00:29:28,799 --> 00:29:30,720
Don't ask what you shouldn't ask.

326
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:38,520
Put on my pajamas for now.

327
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:55,319
Got a cigarette?

328
00:29:55,319 --> 00:29:56,960
No.

329
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:58,440
Then buy me some.

330
00:29:59,119 --> 00:30:00,839
You're sick. You shouldn't smoke.

331
00:30:00,839 --> 00:30:02,079
You...

332
00:30:06,599 --> 00:30:08,240
You damn brat.

333
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:10,280
Why are you meddling so much in my business?

334
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:14,119
Brat.

335
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:17,079
Boss.

336
00:30:17,079 --> 00:30:19,879
The brat saved the beauty again, huh?

337
00:30:21,119 --> 00:30:23,200
Cui Dong Dong, don't say that.

338
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,759
What's going on now?

339
00:30:24,759 --> 00:30:26,039
Why are there police everywhere outside?

340
00:30:26,039 --> 00:30:27,599
You're asking me?

341
00:30:27,599 --> 00:30:29,480
Inspector Hua is dead.

342
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:30,720
What?

343
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:31,920
Inspector Hua is dead.

344
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,319
Yeah.

345
00:30:33,319 --> 00:30:35,759
Weren't you having dinner with him today?

346
00:30:35,759 --> 00:30:36,839
Now he's dead.

347
00:30:36,839 --> 00:30:39,359
Both the underworld
and the police are looking for you.

348
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:42,160
What does that have to do with me?

349
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:43,599
Fei Qi was halfway through the meal

350
00:30:43,599 --> 00:30:45,039
when he suddenly pulled out a gun.

351
00:30:45,039 --> 00:30:46,680
Luckily, I had a gun on me,

352
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:48,400
so I pulled it out and fought back right away.

353
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:49,480
What else was I supposed to do?

354
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:51,079
Then I heard the police arriving.

355
00:30:51,079 --> 00:30:52,880
I didn't want to run into the police,

356
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:55,039
so I jumped out the window and ran.

357
00:30:55,039 --> 00:30:57,599
What about Inspector Hua?

358
00:30:58,359 --> 00:31:00,559
He went to the restroom halfway through.

359
00:31:00,559 --> 00:31:02,240
All right, I got it.

360
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:04,279
Just stay put at the student's place.

361
00:31:04,279 --> 00:31:07,839
His place is so shabby...

362
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:15,880
Are you kidding me?

363
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:16,880
She hung up on me.

364
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:18,079
You...

365
00:31:19,799 --> 00:31:21,640
Go to bed and rest.

366
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:23,159
Go to bed?

367
00:31:24,079 --> 00:31:25,639
I'm going to work.

368
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:29,800
Of course, I know you're going to work.

369
00:31:40,519 --> 00:31:42,720
All right, all right.

370
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:48,000
Ma'am! Ma'am!

371
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:49,559
Have you seen this person?

372
00:31:49,559 --> 00:31:51,279
- No.
- Tell me if you see him.

373
00:31:51,279 --> 00:31:54,240
- Got it.
- Unbelievable. That bastard.

374
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:57,039
Xia Liu Yi, get out here!

375
00:31:57,039 --> 00:31:58,680
Ma'am, have you seen this person?

376
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,720
No.

377
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:01,119
Take a closer look.

378
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:22,279
You're already a grown man,

379
00:33:22,279 --> 00:33:24,520
and you still can't cover yourself properly.

380
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,199
Did I wake you?

381
00:35:23,199 --> 00:35:24,519
No.

382
00:35:29,519 --> 00:35:31,800
You...

383
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,839
Do you want to sleep on the bed?

384
00:35:37,119 --> 00:35:39,760
You...

385
00:35:39,760 --> 00:35:42,080
Do you want to sleep on the bed?

386
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:50,919
Then... Then where will you sleep?

387
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:54,359
Don't tell me I'll sleep on that lousy couch.

388
00:35:58,559 --> 00:36:00,560
So...

389
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:03,560
Where will you sleep?

390
00:36:07,119 --> 00:36:08,599
The bed.

391
00:36:08,599 --> 00:36:10,480
B-E-D. Do you understand?

392
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:13,519
College boy, you're not the only one
who knows English.

393
00:36:14,239 --> 00:36:17,159
When did you even learn English?

394
00:36:17,159 --> 00:36:19,039
How would I know?

395
00:36:19,039 --> 00:36:20,480
Sam.

396
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:22,999
Nice to meet you.

397
00:36:24,199 --> 00:36:25,639
Sam.

398
00:36:25,639 --> 00:36:27,640
Nice to meet you.

399
00:39:38,159 --> 00:39:44,120
Little black dog, you trust me way too quickly.

400
00:40:10,159 --> 00:40:14,760
Brat, your skills are getting better.

401
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:17,039
That's because you're always getting hurt.

402
00:40:18,679 --> 00:40:21,879
Scars are a man's medals.

403
00:40:23,639 --> 00:40:25,599
Forget it.

404
00:40:25,599 --> 00:40:29,079
You've got that gender-emotional
cognition disorder or whatever.

405
00:40:29,079 --> 00:40:30,879
You wouldn't understand.

406
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,360
So annoying.

407
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:35,839
Feels like I didn't sleep all night.

408
00:41:23,039 --> 00:41:24,800
Dad.

409
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,840
It's okay.

410
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:44,319
Don't worry.

411
00:41:59,679 --> 00:42:02,120
I'm so afraid of losing you.

412
00:42:19,639 --> 00:42:21,359
Xia Liu Yi.

413
00:42:22,880 --> 00:42:25,120
Actually, I don't have any emotional disorder.

414
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,439
I just...

415
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:37,760
Like you.

